<plot>"Adaptive Greening" is an investigation of one of the most significant causes of greenhouse gas emissions: construction and energy-inefficient building design. The archiTEXT team begins by explaining the significance of greenhouse gasses, and how they affect the environment. They then continue with explaining how architecture and construction contribute to emissions, and conclude by demonstrating some of the technologies architects can implement in future projects to reduce the environmental impact of their structures.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?023259</url></doc>
